                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.35/8–1045: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-14T10:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 14, 1945—10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1085. There could be no basis for rumor reported in urtel 1815, August 10, 6
                    p.m., in view of fact that there is complete support for your position in the
                    Department. Rockefeller had occasion in meeting with the Ambassador yesterday to
                    express personally his admiration for the outstanding work you have done under
                    difficult circumstances, feeling which the Ambassador professes to share.
                    Memorandum of the conversation<note n="10" xml:id="d278fn10">Not printed.</note>
                    is being sent you airmail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
